title: Inauguration of Joe Biden
added: Senator [[Amy Klobuchar]] delivered the opening remarks, noting the blessing of, only two weeks after an "insurrection", witnessing a stable transition of power on the steps of the Capitol building which she called a "temple" of democracy.

title: Inauguration of Joe Biden
added: Following Custom, Trump is reported to have left a note to his successor on the desk of the Oval Office.

title: Inauguration of Joe Biden
added: The transfer of power included the transition of official administration Twitter accounts, @POTUS and @VP

Members of the Biden-Harris administration are assuming ownership of a number of institutional accounts, including @WhiteHouse, @FLOTUS for first lady Jill Biden and @PressSec for the incoming White House press secretary Jen Psaki.{{cite web|url=https://www.boisestatepublicradio.org/post/inauguration-day-transfer-power-includes-handover-twitter-accounts#stream/0}}

title: Inauguration of Joe Biden
added: The inauguration proceeded without incident.<ref>Philip Athey, [https://www.armytimes.com/news/your-army/2021/01/20/the-national-guard-had-a-quiet-day-in-dc-standing-post-against-threats-they-helped-prevent/ The National Guard had a quiet day in DC standing post against threats they helped prevent], ''Army Times'' (January 20, 2021).</ref><ref>Danielle Wallace & Lucas Y. Tomlinson, [https://www.foxnews.com/us/national-guard-no-confrontations-with-protesters-biden-inauguration-dc National Guard says there were 'no confrontations' with protesters during Biden inauguration], Fox News (January 21, 2021).</ref>

title: Inauguration of Joe Biden
added: After the inauguration, the National Guard began to wind-down operations, arranging for approximately 15,000 of the 25,600 National Guard troops in the District to return home over the next five to ten days, with approximately 7,000 to remain through the end of the month. The demobilization process included checking in equipment, making travel plans, and testing for COVID-19.<ref>Matthew Cox, [https://www.military.com/daily-news/2021/01/21/thousands-of-national-guard-troops-begin-leaving-dc-weekend.html Thousands of National Guard Troops to Begin Leaving DC This Weekend], Military.com (January 21, 2021).</ref><ref>Caitlin M. Kenney, [https://www.stripes.com/news/us/15-000-national-guard-troops-in-dc-to-return-home-soon-1.659424 15,000 National Guard troops in DC to return home soon], ''Stars & Stripes'' (January 21, 2021).</ref>
